# Title: New Root Certificate Installed Via Certutil.EXE
# Author: oscd.community, @redcanary, Zach Stanford @svch0st
# Date: 2023-03-05
# Level: medium
# Description: Detects execution of "certutil" with the "addstore" flag in order to install a new certificate on the system.
# Adversaries may install a root certificate on a compromised system to avoid warnings when connecting to adversary controlled web servers.
# MITRE Tactic: Uncategorized
# Tags: attack.defense-impairment, attack.t1553.004
# Reference: https://github.com/SigmaHQ/sigma/blob/master/rules/windows/process_creation/proc_creation_win_certutil_certificate_installation.yml
# False Positives:
#   - Help Desk or IT may need to manually add a corporate Root CA on occasion. Need to test if GPO push doesn't trigger FP

CommandLine="*-addstore*" OR CommandLine="*/addstore*" OR CommandLine="*–addstore*" OR CommandLine="*—addstore*" OR CommandLine="*―addstore*" CommandLine="*root*" Image="*\\certutil.exe" OR OriginalFileName="CertUtil.exe"